item.title: [HIVE-21799] NullPointerException in DynamicPartitionPruningOptimization, when join key is on aggregation column
item.description:
Following table/query results in NPE:

create table tez_no_dynpart_hashjoin_on_agg(id int, outcome string, eventid int) stored as orc;

explain select a.id, b.outcome from (select id, max(eventid) as event_id_max from tez_no_dynpart_hashjoin_on_agg group by id) a 
LEFT OUTER JOIN tez_no_dynpart_hashjoin_on_agg b 
on a.event_id_max = b.eventid;

item.summary: NullPointerException in DynamicPartitionPruningOptimization, when join key is on aggregation column

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment:
It appears that the GroupByDesc does not seem to have the column mapping information for the join key, in the case that the join key is an aggregation column (it works when the join key is one of the key columns from the GroupBy).

Simple fix is to skip dynamic semijoin reduction optimization if the column mapping for the join key cannot be found in the GroupBy (parentOfRS)

ATTACHMENT ID: 12970350 - PreCommit-HIVE-Build
Hey vgarg, can you review?

The existing logic to get to ExprNode for the given column name seems wrong.

    ColumnInfo columnInfo = parentOfRS.getSchema().getColumnInfo(internalColName);

Above gets to the column info of parentOfRS, assuming parentOfRS is outputting a column named internalColName

 ExprNodeDesc exprNode = null;
    if ( parentOfRS.getColumnExprMap() != null) {
      exprNode = parentOfRS.getColumnExprMap().get(internalColName).clone();
    } else {
      exprNode = new ExprNodeColumnDesc(columnInfo);
    }

But this logic is looking for the same column internalColName in columnExprMap which is a mapping of parentOfRS's input column name to whatever corresponding expression parentOfRS will emit. This will work only if parentRS do not change the input column and output it as it is.

Assuming that internalColName refers to the column coming out of parentOfRS then this should just be

exprNode = new ExprNodeColumnDesc(columnInfo);

I believe this change will also fix the issue here. In fact it should go ahead and create semi join instead of returning.
Thanks for review vgarg. I've updated the patch, as well as the test so that the query should expect to see semijoin reduction optimization.
